########## dial ##########

Add To Every object
  Is
    value  0.
    Not turnable.
End Add To.

Syntax
  turn_to = 'turn' (o) 'to' (n)
    Where n Isa integer
      Else 
        "You can't turn the $1 to $2!"
  

Verb turn_to
  Check o Is turnable
    Else 
      "You can't turn that to anything."
  Does
    If n >999 Then
      "The dial is only marked up to and including 999."
    Else 
      Set value Of o To n.
      "The $1 is now set to $2."
    End If.
End Verb.


The dial Isa object
  At l 
  Has 
    value  0.
  Is 
    turnable.
  Verb examine
    Does
      "The dial is marked with values between 0 and 999. It is currently
       set to"
      Say value Of dial.
      "$$."
  End Verb.
  
End The dial.

The l Isa location
  
End The l.

Start At l.
  "Try 'turn dial to <n>'."
  
